Turn the Night Up is a song recorded by Spanish singer Enrique Iglesias. It was written by Iglesias, Niles Hollowell-Dhar, Marty James and Rome Ramirez and produced by The Cataracs.The song was released to US Top 40 radio on July 22, 2013.On 18 July 2013 Enrique uploaded the single's cover art on his official website.This video was originally shot my Justin Francis, but the record label decided not to go with that video. The reshoot was directed by Yasha Malekzad, and produced by Artist Preserve Ltd. Enrique recently uploaded a fan video, showing various images of his fans snaps and videos of partying. The music video was released on August 19, 2013.Once "Turn Up The Night" impacted airwaves, it immediately garnered an audience of over 12 million within only 24 hours. Meanwhile, over the course of four days, it climbed into the Top 20 audience rank of the Mediabase Top 40.With "Turn the Night Up", Enrique Iglesias posts his second-highest Pop Songs debut, as "Turn the Night Up" charges in at #30.
